e interacting particles at\nthe Sun -- and discuss the implications in terms of potential sources. Our\nanalysis shows that the two proton numbers are poorly correlated, with their\nratio spanning more than five orders of magnitude, suggesting that the back\nprecipitation of shock-acceleration particles is unlikely the source of the\nLDGRF emission.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 30 May 2019 06:58:42 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-07-11"}
